snippet.textDisplay: I don't know if anybody's going to see this or if anybody will take the time to read this but I want to say first off, I hope you all are staying safe during this pandemic. I hope you guys are taking this seriously. The way the virus is rapidly spreading is scary and that's, why we need to all, take the proper precautions such as doing the 5, make sure you are always washing your hands it's unbelievable how many people don't wash there hands and that is the number one way to prevent the virus, also make sure you whenever you sneeze or cough make sure to do it in your elbows*, you don't want to spread it through the air. Make sure you all keep away from your face because that is where the virus enters your body, make sure you are practicing *social distancing*, and stay at home unless you need to buy essentials or if you need to go to work if you can *work from home that would be great. Also even if you are young you still need to take these precautions, you might not be affected as much as older people but you can still get the virus and spread it*, you don't know you have the virus before you've carried it for five days and in those five days, you can spread it to so many people. I know this is completely abnormal and it might be really sad for some of you guys that had plans like I feel really bad for BTS because their whole comeback got ruined, but we all have to work together to fight against this virus. What's scary is that 2 countries have already passed the number of cases in China (where the virus came from) so obviously, it's spreading rapidly and the death tolls keep going up, and many people might not be able to get tested because so many people need to get tested, that's why hospitals are packed, they don't even have enough space for everybody which is really scary to think about. I hope all of you guys are staying safe if anybody that you know has been affected I am so sorry for you guys. Another point please *don't bulk buy many people can't get what they need because too many people are bulk buying. I read a sad story about a man in his 70's that went to buy essentials but he couldn't buy anything because they were all out and he can't go looking 24/7 because his wife had breathing problems and he couldn't get out that much, they used to have a worker but she had to go take care of her own family. Plz consider others and stay safe 💜💜💜
